data.chText: （统称）植物；（尤指某地或环境的）植被，植物群落，草木
data.enText: plants in general, especially the plants that are found in a particular area or environment

data.chText: 这片丘岭草木茂盛，郁郁葱葱。
data.enText: The hills are covered in lush green vegetation.

means: (尤指某地或环境的)植物群落

tr: inactivity that is passive and monotonous, comparable to the inactivity of plant life
example: their holiday was spent in sleep and vegetation

tr: an abnormal growth or excrescence (especially a warty excrescence on the valves of the heart)
all the plant life in a particular region or period
the process of growth in plants

value.def: Plants, trees, and flowers can be referred to as vegetation .

example.ex: The inn has a garden of semi-tropical vegetation.
example.tran: 这家小旅馆里有一个亚热带植物园。
一股植物轻微腐烂的味道
